h3. Summary
When upgrading to JIRA 7.0 from an earlier version with JIRA Service Desk using an invalid license (for example, a *Commercial* JSD license on a JIRA instance with a *Developer* license), no warnings are thrown and the installation of *JIRA Service Desk* is possible.

After the installation, accessing a project of type *Service Desk* throws a 500 error.

!500_sd_unlicensed.png|thumbnail!

Also, accessing *Administration > Applications > Versions & licenses* shows no problem with the license.

!incompatible_licenses.png|thumbnail!

h3. Expected Behavior
* Display an "Invalid License" page when accessing the project;
* Display an warning when installing JSD;
* Display an error on "Versions & licenses" page;

h3. Actual Behavior
* 500 error when accessing a SD project;
* No warnings;

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Setup a JIRA 6.4.x with JIRA Service Desk using an invalid/incompatible license;
# Upgrade to JIRA 7.0 (using the JIRA Software or Core installer);
# Go to *Administration > Applications > Versions & licenses*;
# Install JIRA Service Desk 3.0 (application);
# Go to a SD project;

h3. Workaround
# Go to *Administration > Applications > Versions & licenses*;
# Apply a valid license for JIRA Service Desk, of the same type of other licenses in JIRA;

h3. Alternative workaround
# Go to *Administration > Applications > Versions & licenses*;
# Delete the license for JIRA Service Desk;

